In[10]:
sns.set_style("darkgrid")
numerical_columns = df.select_dtypes(include=["int64","float64"]).columns

plt.figure(figsize=(14, len(numerical_columns)*3))
for idx, feature in enumerate(numerical_columns,1):
    plt.subplot(len(numerical_columns), 2, idx)
    sns.histplot(df[feature], kde=True)
    plt.title(f"{feature} | Skewness: {round(df[feature].skew(),2)}")

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
In[11]:
numerical_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['int64','float64']).columns
stat_analysis = pd.DataFrame({
    'Skewness': [df[col].skew() for col in numerical_cols],
    'Kurtosis': [df[col].kurtosis() for col in numerical_cols]
}, index=numerical_cols)

stat_analysis['Abs_Skewness'] = stat_analysis['Skewness'].abs()
stat_analysis = stat_analysis.sort_values('Abs_Skewness', ascending=False).drop('Abs_Skewness', axis=1)

stat_analysis

In[12]:
def format_price(x, p):
    return f'${x/1e6:.1f}M'

plt.figure(figsize=(10,8))
sns.boxplot(x="grade of the house", y="Price", data=df, palette='viridis')
plt.title('Price Distribution by Grade of the House')
plt.xlabel('Grade')
plt.ylabel('Price')
plt.gca().yaxis.set_major_formatter(FuncFormatter(format_price))
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

In[14]:
numerical_cols = df.select_dtypes(include=['int64','float64']).columns
corr_matrix = df[numerical_cols].corr()

plt.figure(figsize=(14,9))
mask = np.triu(np.ones_like(corr_matrix, dtype=bool))
sns.heatmap(corr_matrix, mask=mask, annot=True, fmt='.2f', cmap='coolwarm',
            linewidths=0.7, cbar_kws={'shrink':0.8})
plt.title("Correlation Heatmap (Numerical Features)", fontsize=14)
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import locale

# Set Indian Locale for number formatting
locale.setlocale(locale.LC_ALL, 'en_IN.UTF-8')

def format_indian(value):
    return locale.format_string("%d", value, grouping=True)

print(f"Average Price: {format_indian(int(df['Price'].mean()))}")
print(f"Median Price: {format_indian(int(df['Price'].median()))}")
